OL,3,CWarning issued as increase in battery
OL,4,Cexplosions and fires across
OL,5,CWarwickshire
OL,7,FWarwickshire Fire and Rescue service
OL,8,Fhas issued a stark warning urging
OL,9,Fresidents to take precautions when
OL,10,Fusing and disposing of lithium-ion
OL,11,Fbatteries.
OL,13,FIt comes following a rise in fires
OL,14,Fcaused by batteries across the county.
OL,16,FThe force said lithium-ion batteries
OL,17,Fcan be dangerous and contain highly
OL,18,Fflammable materials - despite this,
OL,19,Fthey power many of our everyday
OL,20,Fdevices, from smartphones and laptops
OL,21,Fto e-scooters and electric vehicles.
